<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="5">
<Content>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>EXT. WILDFIRE RIDGE - DUSK</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A wall of orange stretches across the horizon. Smoke billows thousands of feet into the sky, turning sunset into apocalypse. Embers drift like snow.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A HOTSHOT CREW (20 firefighters in yellow Nomex) digs a fire line along the ridge. They work in silence, exhaustion painted on every face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>CAPTAIN MAYA CHEN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>We've got thirty minutes before the wind shifts. Hold the line or we lose the town.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>DIAZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Copy. East flank is holding but the brush is bone dry. One spot fire and we're running.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Maya pulls up a weather app on her radio-mounted tablet. The wind forecast has shifted RED.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>CAPTAIN MAYA CHEN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>All units, prepare safety zones. This thing is about to crown.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>INT. INCIDENT COMMAND POST - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A makeshift operations center in a high school gymnasium. Maps cover every wall. Radio chatter fills the room. INCIDENT COMMANDER WALSH (50s, rumpled, running on coffee) studies a satellite feed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>WALSH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Where's Chen's crew?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>OPERATIONS OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Still on the ridge. She's requesting air support but we've grounded all birds until visibility improves.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>WALSH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>She's got twenty people up there with no air cover and a wind shift coming. Get me CalFire on the line. Now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>EXT. WILDFIRE RIDGE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>The wind hits. The fire ROARS to life, crowning through the treetops. A wall of flame fifty feet high races toward the crew.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>CAPTAIN MAYA CHEN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>SAFETY ZONES! MOVE! MOVE!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>The crew scrambles. Tools dropped, packs abandoned. They sprint toward a clearing two hundred yards downhill.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>DIAZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Rookie! Where's Torres?!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>ROOKIE FIREFIGHTER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>He was on the east flank! I lost sight of him!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Maya stops running. Looks back at the wall of fire consuming the ridge where Torres was working. A decision forms on her face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>DIAZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Maya, don't. Don't do it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>CAPTAIN MAYA CHEN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Get the crew to safety. That's an order.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>She pulls her fire shelter from her pack and runs back toward the flames.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<Text>EXT. BURNED RIDGE - DAWN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Smoke rises from blackened earth. Everything is ash and charcoal. The fire has passed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>A search team picks through the wreckage. Diaz leads them, face streaked with soot and dried tears.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>DIAZ</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Maya! Torres! Sound off!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Nothing. Then — a faint TAPPING. Metal on metal. Coming from beneath a deployed fire shelter thirty yards east.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text>Diaz sprints to the shelter and pulls it back. Maya and Torres lie underneath, burned but alive. Maya's hands are blistered, clutching Torres's collar.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text>CAPTAIN MAYA CHEN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text>(barely audible)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text>Told you... I'd hold the line.</Text>
</Paragraph>
</Content>
</FinalDraft>
